{"ts":"2026-06-07T05:50:59.489Z","author":"telemetry-compat-subagent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/2","value":{"created_at":"2026-06-07T05:50:59.489Z","author":"telemetry-compat-subagent","text":"Telemetry compatibility sub-agent evidence: investigated GitHub issue #138 and confirmed the old shape failed because Commander only accepted one telemetry positional before runTelemetry dispatch. Implemented parser-level alias support in src/cli/register-operations.ts so pm telemetry local-analytics <status|flush|stats|clear> maps to the existing pm telemetry <subcommand> implementation, with status as the default for bare local-analytics. Added real-CLI regression coverage in tests/integration/config-positional-cli.integration.spec.ts and documented the legacy namespace in docs/COMMANDS.md. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/config-positional-cli.integration.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/telemetry-command.spec.ts (2 files, 9 tests); pnpm contracts:check in the real repository context. Manual isolated smoke passed with temporary PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH for status, stats, flush, and clear via node dist/cli.js telemetry local-analytics <subcommand> --json. Note: pm test --run passed build and focused tests, but its linked pnpm contracts:check invocation failed only under the schema sandbox with a stale fixture message; the same contract check passes in the real repo context where active contracts are evaluated."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-07T05:50:59.489Z"}],"before_hash":"146c41be9f618ac601c2ab4e8f76b0e83c1e908b834955592cea91e9b4f65731","after_hash":"7d8649ffe5fd1aac165e1991a21b49ffd7e1adb643d0ea116f9c83317db31a50"}
